This workspace is the **strategy-automation** repo. Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) for the full agent brief. Highlights:

- Surfaces covered: Mosaic data models, classic / legacy semantic layer, runtime analytics, cubes/datasets, admin platform, AI agents, data validation.
- Platform goal: complete automation coverage wherever Strategy exposes an API, SDK, MCP, CLI, or reproducible hook. Classify gaps using `memory/reference_strategy_automation_coverage.md`.
- Entry skills: `skill/SKILL.md` (build-mosaic-model), `strategy-automation/SKILL.md` (NLQ router), `strategy-validation/SKILL.md` (data validation).
- Durable knowledge indexed at `memory/MEMORY.md` — load files on demand.
- Credentials + tenant values come from env vars (`MSTR_BASE`, `MSTR_USER`, `MSTR_PASSWORD`, `MSTR_PROJECT_ID`/`MSTR_PROJECT_NAME`, `MSTR_DEST_FOLDER_ID`). Never hardcode.
- Consumer-grade naming + paired-query validation are part of the ship bar. Validation is comparator-dependent; if no trusted comparator exists yet, mark it pending instead of calling the build shippable. See `memory/feedback_consumer_grade_naming.md` and `memory/reference_strategy_data_validation.md`.
- MCP tools (`get_projects`, `get_mosaic_models`, `get_semantics`, `query`) configured separately through your Cursor MCP settings. This repo references them by name only.
